# Artifacts Routing Policy

Use `https://github.com/davechogan/Artifacts.git` for non-release assets.

## Decision rule

- If a file is required for app runtime, build, or CI: keep it in this app repo.
- If a file is historical, investigative, environment-specific, or snapshot data: store it in `Artifacts.git`.

## Artifact mapping (required)

| Artifact type | Target in Artifacts repo |
|---|---|
| Architecture plans, implementation specs | `projects/<project-slug>/plans/` |
| Investigation notes, postmortems | `projects/<project-slug>/plans/` |
| One-off helper scripts (non-runtime) | `projects/<project-slug>/scripts/` |
| DB snapshots/backups (compressed) | `projects/<project-slug>/db_snapshots/<YYYY-MM-DD>/` |
| Exports (CSV/JSON), ad hoc reports | `projects/<project-slug>/exports/<YYYY-MM-DD>/` |
| Diagnostic logs | `projects/<project-slug>/logs/<YYYY-MM-DD>/` |
| Provenance/checksums/restore metadata | `projects/<project-slug>/metadata/` |

## Required controls for DB snapshots

- Prefer compressed snapshots (`.zst`/`.gz`), not raw DB when possible.
- Include `SHA256SUMS.txt` for each snapshot batch.
- Include provenance metadata (`source repo`, `commit`, `timestamp`, `author`, `artifact list`).
- Never store secrets/credentials.

## New project onboarding

When creating artifacts for a new project:

1. Clone/open `Artifacts.git`.
2. Run scaffold:
   - `scripts/new_project.sh <project-slug> [source-repo-url]`
3. Add first artifacts under `projects/<project-slug>/...`.
4. Commit and push in `Artifacts.git`.

## Do not commit to app repo

- `data/*.db`, backup DB snapshots, local logs, exported CSV/JSON artifacts.
- Machine-local workspace files and worktree internals.
- Any artifact that is not needed to run/test/release the app.
